{
  "stem": "747.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when it was after midnight, with a hungry stomach, you work all night, it was very difficult to be-- be alert and be careful.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "By that time, I was with a group of women from all over Europe.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a little United Nations.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The only-- the common language was German that we all understood.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But otherwise, we were from all from a different country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we sung in the middle of the night, not to fall asleep.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And telling stories.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that-- really I can say that saved my sanity.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that few hours that we had inside in the block, finally we got home-- one week we worked night shift, and the other worked daytime.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And when we were finally on our bed, it was-- it was-- we're trying to keep each other alive and the spirit alive.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they're talking about books, about films, about things what happened in our own country-- and performing, and dancing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was one young lady from Greece, her name was Eva, she was a ballet dancer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She was performing to us, I mean, in a hungry stomach.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But it just was a distraction-- you know, something divide the attention from the-- from the reality what was there, facing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then came Hanukkah, and we decided that, against all odds, we have to light a Hanukkah candle.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we pulled together that little match, what we got once a week, Sundays, and pulled out the thread from our blanket, and lit the candles-- singing the-- and then telling about what happened thousands of years ago to our ancestors, hoping that they made it-- hopefully that we will find liberation coming our way, too.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And it was a close, very close, between the inmates.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
